.TH sstat 1 "May 2025" "sstat 1.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
sstat \- display file or file system status in Shamsi (Jalali)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sstat
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] <\fIPATHS\fR>...

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sstat
displays information about the specified file(s) or directory(s), with timestamps converted to the Shamsi (Jalali) calendar.
It is part of the modern Rust implementation of the classic jcal utilities, aiming to provide functionality similar to \fBstat\fR(1) but with Jalali dates.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-p, --persian-output\fR
Display Farsi numbers and names for dates.
.TP
\fB-l, --ls-format\fR
Display in a format similar to \fBls -lT\fR. This shows detailed information including permissions, owner, group, size, and last modification time.
.TP
\fB-n, --no-newline\fR
Do not print a trailing newline character after the output.
.TP
\fB-r, --raw-format\fR
Display raw numerical information (e.g., timestamps as Unix epochs) without Shamsi conversion for dates.
.TP
\fB-x, --verbose-format\fR
Display verbose information about the file, including access, modification, and change times in Shamsi.
.TP
\fB-s, --shell-format\fR
Display information in a shell-friendly format, suitable for use with `eval`.
.TP
\fB-h, --help\fR
Print help information.
.TP
\fB-V, --version\fR
Print version information.

.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
<\fIPATHS\fR>...
One or more file or directory paths to get the status of.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sstat /path/to/file
Show the status of /path/to/file with Shamsi dates.
.TP
.B sstat -l /path/to/directory
Display detailed information for /path/to/directory in `ls -lT` like format with Shamsi dates.
.TP
.B sstat -x file1 file2
Display verbose status information for file1 and file2 with Shamsi dates.
.TP
.B sstat -p *.txt
Display status for all .txt files in the current directory with Persian numbers and names for dates.

